alvarionQOS.contactinfo: Alvarion Ltd. Postal: 21a HaBarzel St. P.O. Box 13139 Tel-Aviv 69710 Israel Phone: +972 3 645 6262
alvarionQOS.description: The MIB module for enterprise specific QoS options.

coQOSCountersTable.name: coQOSCountersTable
coQOSCountersTable.description: Group containing attributes that are MAC counters. In tabular form to allow multiple instance on an agent.

coQOSCountersEntry.name: coQOSCountersEntry
coQOSCountersEntry.description: An entry in the coQOSCountersEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coQOSQueueId.name: coQOSQueueId
coQOSQueueId.description: Queue identifier used to access the statistics.

coQOSTransmittedFrameCount.name: coQOSTransmittedFrameCount
coQOSTransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter increments only when an acknowledged MPDU with an individual address in the address 1 field or MPDU with a multicast address in the address 1 field of type Data or Management.

coQOSMulticastTransmittedFrameCount.name: coQOSMulticastTransmittedFrameCount
coQOSMulticastTransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter increments only when the multicast bit is set in the destination MAC address of a successfully transmitted MSDU. When operating as a STA in an ESS, where these frames are directed to the AP, this implies having received an acknowledgment to all associated MPDUs.

coQOSFailedCount.name: coQOSFailedCount
coQOSFailedCount.description: This counter increments when an MSDU is not transmitted successfully due to the number of transmit attempts exceeding either the coQOSShortRetryLimit or coQOSLongRetryLimit.

coQOSRetryCount.name: coQOSRetryCount
coQOSRetryCount.description: This counter increments when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after one or more retransmissions. This is basically a total of single and multiple retry counts.

coQOSMultipleRetryCount.name: coQOSMultipleRetryCount
coQOSMultipleRetryCount.description: This counter increments when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after more than one retransmission.

coQOSFrameDuplicateCount.name: coQOSFrameDuplicateCount
coQOSFrameDuplicateCount.description: This counter increments when a frame is received that the Sequence Control field indicates is a duplicate.

coQOSReceivedFrameCount.name: coQOSReceivedFrameCount
coQOSReceivedFrameCount.description: This counter shall be incremented for each successfully received MPDU of type Data or Management. This is basically a total of unicast and multicast received frames.

coQOSMulticastReceivedFrameCount.name: coQOSMulticastReceivedFrameCount
coQOSMulticastReceivedFrameCount.description: This counter shall increment when a MPDU is received with the multicast bit set in the destination MAC address.

coQOSCompliance.name: coQOSCompliance
coQOSCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities that implement the IEEE 802.11 MIB.

coQOSCountersGroup.name: coQOSCountersGroup
coQOSCountersGroup.description: Provides the necessary support for QOS counters.
